THE Toyota bakkie was carrying eight passengers and travelling from Groblersdal to Jane Furse in Limpopo. Five people died in the crash on Sunday in Nebo outside Groblersdal. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said the bakkie reportedly crashed into a stationary truck at Glen Cowie Village just opposite St Rita's Hospital. “Five people from the bakkie died instantly whereas, two other people were seriously injured. The driver suffered minor injuries,” Ngoepe said.  According to Ngoepe only one passenger from the truck survived the incident unharmed. In a statement, Ngoepe said police investigations revealed that when the incident happened, the driver of the truck had gone to look for help after a mechanical breakdown. “Police have opened a case of culpable homicide and the circumstances leading to the accident are unknown at this stage,” Ngoepe.  